import random
# Select 4 random days
random_days = random.sample(range(samples.shape[0]), 4)

# Create a figure with subplots
fig, axes = plt.subplots(4, 6, figsize=(20, 8))

for i, day in enumerate(random_days):
    # Compute common color scale for this row only (target + samples for this day)
    target_day = np.flip(target[variable][day].values, axis=0)
    samples_day = samples[day, 0, :, :, :].cpu().numpy()
    vmin_row = min(target_day.min(), samples_day.min())
    if variable == "pr":
        vmax_row = max(target_day.max(), samples_day.max()) * 0.9
    else:
        vmax_row = max(target_day.max(), samples_day.max())
    
    # Plot target
    axes[i, 0].imshow(target_day, cmap='viridis_r', vmin=vmin_row, vmax=vmax_row)
    axes[i, 0].set_title(f'Day {day}: Target')
    axes[i, 0].axis('off')
    
    # Plot 5 samples
    for j in range(5):
        axes[i, j+1].imshow(samples[day, 0, :, :, j].cpu().numpy(), cmap='viridis_r', vmin=vmin_row, vmax=vmax_row)
        axes[i, j+1].set_title(f'Sample {j}')
        axes[i, j+1].axis('off')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Calculate spatial mean across y and x dimensions for samples and target
samples_mean = samples[:, :, :, :, :].mean(dim=(2, 3)) if hasattr(samples, 'mean') else samples[:, :, :, :, 0].cpu().numpy().reshape(samples.shape[0], samples.shape[1], -1).mean(axis=2)
if domain == "ALPS":
    target_mean = target[variable].mean(dim=('y', 'x'))
else:
    target_mean = target[variable].mean(dim=('lat', 'lon'))

# Convert to numpy if needed
if hasattr(samples_mean, 'numpy'):
    samples_mean = samples_mean.numpy()
else:
    samples_mean = samples_mean.cpu().numpy() if hasattr(samples_mean, 'cpu') else samples_mean

# Plot time series
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
for i in range(samples.shape[-1]):
    plt.plot(samples_mean[:600, ...,i], label=f'Sample {i}', alpha=0.7)
plt.plot(target_mean.values[:600], label='Target', linewidth=2, color='black')
plt.xlabel('Time')
plt.ylabel(f'{variable} (K)')
plt.title('Spatial Mean Time Series: Samples vs Target')
plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
